args: Ya got a real knack for statin' the obvious.
Folks call this ＂the village the goddess\nabandoned.＂ Nothin' but despair out here.
I'm going to change this village\nfor the better...
Urgh... Gimme five more minutes...\nAnd stop pulling the covers off...
Why, so ya can sleep in past noon?\nGet up and eat breakfast already!
You need to lay off the caffeine.
Just get your damn butt in gear!
All right, all right. I'm up.
*sigh* You sounded so full of yourself\nin my dream, but this is the reality.
Urgh... I wanna go back to bed...
Good morning, Yaten. I see you got a\nrather rude awakening today, too.
Anything I can do to help, Cleo?
I appreciate the thought, but I'm fine.\nYou should get some rest.
Meanwhile, Natalie is very much a\nmorning type. Which is good for us, but...
Yeah, I'm amazed these two can work\ntogether, what with bein' total opposites.
Get it together already—you have to\nget that entire float finished today!
I gotta eat, then get over there and put\nthe finishing touches on everything!
He clearly does nothing in half-measures.
Indeed. Festivals turn him into a different\nperson entirely.
I've sworn to never lift a finger\nunless a festival's involved.
That's nothing to boast about, ya dope!\nNow if you're done stuffin' your face,\nwe're gettin' outta here!
I brought you something to eat, Natalie.
Hmm? Is Yaten not with you?
He's probably off seein' how all\nthe stalls are comin' along.
He knows I can handle this.
You aren't even considering the possibility\nthat he might be slacking off?
Heh. Not when it comes to a festival.\nIf he was that kinda guy, I wouldn't be\nhere now.
See, I was born in a charming place known\nas ＂the village the goddess abandoned.＂
It was so poor, we didn't even have a\nchurch. Oh, and my mother eventually\nran out and left me on my own.
Then you were raised in an orphanage?
Orphanage? Hah! We didn't have\none of those either.
Everyone looked out for themselves.\nThat's just how it was.
Wasn't time to be looking after others.
I was just a kid, but I still did things\nin order to live. ...BAD things.
But just as I was gettin' sick of the life,\nmy pal Yaten showed up.
I'm going to change this village\nfor the better...
What this place needs is a festival!
Well, THAT caught me off guard.
And did his plan actually work?\nWas it truly so simple?
Oh, it was anything BUT simple.
No one would give the guy the time'a\nday at first—yours truly included.
But then he said somethin' that\njust sorta...stuck with me.

He said that if our village was abandoned
by the goddess, that meant we could hold
the craziest festival ever because she
wouldn't be watchin'!
Aaah ha ha! Guess I shouldn't have said\nthat in front of a Paladyn, yeah?
Anyway, at the time it sounded\nlike a total hoot.
Pretty soon, the whole village turned out\nto help throw the festival together.
And people were... They were SMILING.\nI ain't never seen that before!
Yaten's festival drew a huge crowd,\nand our little village grew into a town.
I had no idea festivals could have\nquite so profound an effect.
That makes two of us. Ya coulda knocked\nme over with a feather when I saw it.
Found myself thinkin' that maybe this\nfestival gig was the kinda life I wanted.

So when Yaten left town, I followed.
He tried to shoo me away at first,
but eventually he took me on as a
kind of assistant-slash-apprentice.
He must have been a challenging master.
Ha! Was and is still! But that's just the\nprice ya pay what for fallin' in love.
What? No! Gross!\nI love his FESTIVALS.
I mean, look at this float decoration.\nYaten spent DAYS on it.
It is stunning—and so delicately finished!
But the design looks somehow familiar...
He based it on one of this town's\ntraditional designs.
He's always saying how festivals belong to\nthe town they're held in, which is why ya\ngotta work local stuff in.
His passion really is second to none.
For festivals, at least. Rest of the time,\nhe's just a hopeless slob.
But I love what he creates, and I'm happy\nto give my all to see it happen.
Just hearing you speak so makes me\nanticipate this festival all the more.
